<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-12 px-0">
            <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-12 px-0">
                <a onclick="runCriteo()" href="/login/?returnurl=/VacancyApplication/ExternalApplication/2367326" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary w-100">Apply</a>
            </div>
</div>            <a href="#" class="mt-10 d-inline-block" aria-label="Print" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="This company only accepts applications on their career portal. You may be required to re-enter your details on their site. We wont be able to track it under your 'Application History' ">External Application<i class="fas fa-info-circle ml-2"></i></a>


    
        <hr>
        <div class="row c24-vacancy-details">
            <div class="col">
                <h1 class=" text-left  mt-0">Vacancy Details</h1>
                        <p class="mb-15">Employer: <a href="/"><strong>Provincial Logistics</strong></a></p>


                    <div class="v-descrip">
                        <p><strong><em>Provincial Group, a well-established warehousing and logistics operation in Paarl</em></strong><span>, is seeking a proactive and detail-oriented Transport Controller to join their operations team. This role is ideal for an energetic individual who thrives in a fast-paced environment and is eager to grow within transport operations.</span></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>KPA’s include (but are not limited to):</strong><span> *Coordinate and allocate part loads and courier deliveries across various routes *Manage daily truck schedules, manifests, and waybill administration *Liaise with drivers, depots, and clients to ensure efficient operations *Support consolidation planning and transport system updates *Monitor courier movements and delivery performance *Build and maintain strong client relationships through regular communication *Contribute to achieving and improving operational turnover and gross profit targets *All other tasks related to this role.</span></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Essential qualifications, skills and experience:</strong></p> <p><span>• Grade 12 (Matric);</span></p> <p><span>• Minimum 3 years’ experience in a transport, logistics, courier, or last-mile environment;</span></p> <p><span>• Experience with transport planning, route coordination, and fleet operations;</span></p> <p><span>• Proficiency in Microsoft Office and transport management systems (DataTim experience advantageous);</span></p> <p><span>• Strong organisational, communication, and problem-solving skills;</span></p> <p><span>• Ability to perform effectively under pressure in a dynamic operational environment;</span></p> <p><span>• Valid Code 8 driver’s licence advantageous;</span></p> <p><span>• Experience in the wine industry will be beneficial.</span></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Advantageous:</strong></p> <p><span>• Courier or logistics technology platforms.</span></p> <p><span>• POD (Proof of Delivery) workflows.</span></p> <p><span>• Consolidation planning principles.</span></p> <p><span>• Previous experience managing or improving turnover and GP targets.</span></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Please apply online at www.m3online.co.za before 09:00 on 26 June 2026.</strong></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><span>For general enquiries, contact our team at M3 Human Capital Management on XXX-XXXX.</span></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><em>Please note that only shortlisted candidates are contacted. If no feedback is received within two weeks of the closing date, please assume that your application was unsuccessful.</em></p>
                    </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <hr>


    





